author: AccessWDUN Staff
title: Volleyball: Jefferson clinches state berth with win over E. Jackson
text:
By AccessWDUN Staff Related Articles Volleyball: Lady Vikings claim second straight 7-AAA crown Volleyball: Gainesville opens 8- tourney with win Volleyball: North Hall finishes with No. 3 seed from 8-AAAA Volleyball: North Hall moves on in Area tournament 
The Jefferson volleyball team advanced to the state tournament on Friday via a 25-14, 26-24 win over rival East Jackson in the Area 8-AAA tournament. 
Abby Wood had 8 kills and 10 digs to lead the Lady Dragons, while Lindsey Nilsen had 6 kills. Madison Corbett had 16 asists. 
Jefferson next faces Oconee County at 11:45 a.m. Saturday in The Arena at Jefferson. Associated Tags : High school volleyball, Jefferson volleyball Â© Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
